ר   ווב ו / and may Godòs glory fill all the earth. The mean-
ing of the Hebrew phrase is rich in ambiguity. All earth is filled with
divine glory, but divine glory itself is filled up with earthliness. It is the
reality of this world that fills Godòs presence, as it is the presence that
gives the world its glory.    /SC/XXA.G./XX/PR

