/PG234/XX/PR

The soul of every living thing shall bless your name, /SCE/XXTERNAL
/XXO/XXNE/XX, our God, the spirit of all flesh shall glorify and hold in
reverence continually the memory of you, our sovereign one.
From one eternity to another, you alone are God. For without
you, we have no ruler, no redeemer, none to champion our cause,
none to rescue or to save, none to nourish or to nurture us,
whatever be the hour, or the trouble, or the need./PI/PR

/SCC/XXOMMENTARY./XX /ITNishmat Kol H/±ay/XX consists of three sections. The first section presents Godòs
unity as that unity is declared with every breath of creation. The second
section gives thanks for timely rains and declares God to be beyond
creationòs collective ability to praise. Even if we could enlist natureòs great-
est capacities in the service of praising God, they would still fall short.
Praise "as great as all outdoors" is still inadequate./PR

/PR

In the third section of /ITNishmat Kol H/±ay/XX, Israelòs unique praises reflect its
historical experiences of God as the power that brings redemption. /ITNishmat
Kol H/±ay/XX begins with a universal chorus of praise, moves to the particular
praise of Israel, and then speaks of the many ways that individual actions
serve as praise. Praises arise from the universe /ITwithin/XX the self just as they
fill the universe /ITwithout/XX. Verses from the Psalms illustrate aspects of body
and breath/soul contributing praises that fill worlds./PR

/PR

/ITPesukey Dezimrah/XX ends with this rabbinic composition reassembling indi-
vidual voices into a chorus of adoration and thanksgiving. The final para-
graphs are a reprise of the first blessing of /ITPesukey Dezimrah/XX in /ITBaruh/±
Sheòamar/XX (page 177). Thus, the entire collection beginning with /ITBaruh/±
Sheòamar/XX and ending before the Kaddish (which separates /ITPesukey
Dezimrah/XX from /ITShah/±arit/XX) becomes a well defined literary whole.    /SC/XXS.S./XX/PR

/PR

Nishmat is the song of the wave/PR

awakening to the ocean,/PR

seeing that the wave is the ocean and the ocean the wave,/PR

recognizing the interdependence of all things and/PR

discovering the awesome wonder that is our reality.    /SC/XXR.M.S./XX/PR

